:{{DIcon}} I want to chat with you...
::<!--Trigger PerformanceE 502017103: Config/Level/NPCDialogue/P10202/F10202001_G43/Act/Act_502017103.json-->
::'''Cong:''' Alright. It's not like I have any inspiration, is it... What are you after? Is it about artifex technology?
::<!--Custom String Trigger: 502017103_Option-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: 502017103_Option-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} You know artifex technology?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017120-->
:::'''Cong:''' Yeah, I'm an artisan at the Artisanship Commission, and I'm kind of a big deal. My boss loves me and he said, "Cong, if you just work on your EQ a little, you'll be a Master Artisan in another hundred years."
:::'''Cong:''' But honestly, I hate hearing that. In this day and era, why are there still stereotyped notions that engineers have high IQ and low EQ?
:::'''Cong:''' Ack... But that's all a load of bull. If only my poetry were half as good as my artifex skills, I wouldn't be so anxious right now.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Everyone's got their own strengths.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017124-->
::::'''Cong:''' That may be true, but it doesn't fix my problem. *sigh*...
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Artifex skills can also be used to write poetry.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017126-->
::::'''Cong:''' ...To tell you the truth, that's what I think, too. I'm trying to find a way to do just that.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Why are you so obsessed with writing poetry?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017128-->
:::'''Cong:''' Well, it's not for her... I don't really know you, so I don't want to say too much.
:::'''Cong:''' Anyway, I like this girl. But she doesn't like guys like me... The guys she likes use strange melodies to string together all these strange words, and they just recite them all from memory...
:::'''Cong:''' In short... this girl loves poets. However, as you can see, I'm slightly lacking when it comes to the poetry department.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Have you tried any other forms of literature?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017132-->
:::'''Cong:''' Yeah, I tried some Xianzhou sonnets... What do you think about this one?
:::'''Cong:''' "Emerald mounts hold a love fledgling, but I'm way more handsome than Yanqing. So annoying, yet you make my heart sing, you pretty thing."
:::'''Cong:''' I feel like sonnets allow me to express myself more freely, and produce a more polished result than poetry. What do you think?
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Beautifully written.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017136-->
::::'''Cong:''' That means we have similar taste. I showed it to my boss, but he just told me to shred it up, swallow it, and never show it to anyone ever again.
::::'''Cong:''' He's so weird. We already have a shredder in the Artisanship Commission.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} ...this word, "Yanqing," seems a little abrupt.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017139-->
::::'''Cong:''' You have such a bad understanding of poetry, and you're trying to appraise poems?
::::'''Cong:''' I mention "Yanqing" here as a literary device. I'm saying here that I'm even more handsome, dashing, and graceful than the genius fighter...
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Yeah? Why do I feel slightly disgusted?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017142-->
::::'''Cong:''' ...
::::'''Cong:''' I feel attacked, but totally acceptable. Thank you for your honesty.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} I think writing poetry requires some training.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017145-->
:::'''Cong:''' I know what you mean. This is just the same as developing new artifex tech. Poetry has its rules and techniques. As long as I can solve these problems, then I'll have achieved that level of training.
:::'''Cong:''' The rules refer to the special rhythm upon which Xianzhou poetry relies. As long as all the different permutations that conform to the rhythm can be exhaustively listed out, then we can define the limits of this rule.
:::'''Cong:''' These rules are a piece of cake, and it's the techniques that're particularly hard. But no matter who I ask, they always come back to me with "you can't talk about technique with poetry. That's not romantic." But can't technology be romantic, too?
:::'''Cong:''' For example: "On the staff the goldsmith waves large profit obese, white paper flies stages to rescue the goose"... This is the most humanistic verse I've strung together out of the automated word-combination logarithms. I don't understand what it's trying to say, but can't you sense the elegance of technology here?
:::'''Cong:''' As for artisans at the Artisanship Commission, failure is a required step on the road to success. I'll try some other things out once I'm prepared.
:::'''Cong:''' I'll have to keep trying to write poetry on my own until I come up with a better way... *sigh* writing poems sure is difficult.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} I have nothing else to ask.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502017152-->
:::'''Cong:''' So long. Catch you again later.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: 502017103_END-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: 502017103_END-->
:::<!--Ends the current performance-->
