::'''Cong:''' Oh, that one. The Gloomy Poet. Have you found any clues about it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} When you put it like that, it sounds like there are multiple poets?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021504-->
:::'''Cong:''' Mmm, that's right. I made several other poets besides the gloomy one.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Y&mdash;you can't be serious about getting them all back, can you?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021506-->
:::'''Cong:''' Of course I want them all back!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I know where the Baroumbrella is...
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021508-->
:::'''Cong:''' Excellent. I never thought I'd get such a speedy reply.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} No clues at the moment &mdash; but I can help you out.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021510-->
:::'''Cong:''' That's great! I've always wanted a good helper just like you!
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_202021511-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021511-->
::'''Cong:''' They say, "Gloominess is the backbone of poetry." If a poet is melancholic enough, the most beautiful poetic verse will flow out... I had such high hopes for this Gloomy Poet.
::'''Cong:''' I set its Gloomy setting very high, and it ended up wailing for half a day at the sight of a buttonhole missing a button.
::'''Cong:''' In the end, just like all other artistic youths, it got lost in the hustle and bustle of city life before it ever got the chance to write a decent piece... Ahem, I hope circumstances haven't forced it to have to get a job. That wouldn't be very poetic, would it?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} When we met, it was very sentimental.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021515-->
:::'''Cong:''' Sounds like it hasn't forgotten its roots... But it's time for it to come home.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} It's so depressed that it can't communicate at all.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021517-->
:::'''Cong:''' That's not really the case here. While being overly depressed is a serious illness for humans, for an ingenium it counts as a malfunction.
:::'''Cong:''' That's why the Xianzhou expressly prohibits most ingenia from imitating human emotion. Emotions are not only superfluous to machines &mdash; they are dangerous.
:::'''Cong:''' *sigh* I have my reasons for wanting it to be depressed, so I'm stuck bringing despair to this bot.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Don't be so dramatic. Give it a whack and it'll be fine.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021521-->
:::'''Cong:''' If you break it, then you have to pay me for labor and materials.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_202021522-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_202021522-->
::'''Cong:''' Come on {{MC|f=miss|m=mister}}, help me out. {{Color|keyword|nobold=1|Open up its back flap, find its jade abacus core, and give it a solid repair job}}.
::'''Cong:''' As long as you can reduce the Gloomy setting, it'll probably come back with you.
::<!--Ends the current performance-->
